Text.Value: Say, where's Karlach? She didn't abandon us, did she?
Karlach's gone? Couldn't hack it, no doubt.
Karlach was here when I went to sleep... Where is she?
Karlach? Karlach? Where'd she run off to?
Huh. Where's Karlach?
I wouldn't worry. We're better off without him.
He left. Didn't say why.
She rushed off this morning. Probably some infernal business.
Rushed off this morning. He probably remembered an overdue book.
Hold on, where's Gale? The air feels a little less... magical.
Gale's run off, then? Couldn't hack it, no doubt.
We're short a head - where's Gale?
Gale? Gale? Where's he run off to?
Huh. Where's Gale?
I wouldn't worry. We're better off without her.
Say, where's Shadowheart? She didn't abandon us, did she?
Hey, where's Shadowheart? I was looking forward to annoying her today.
Shadowheart's gone? I should have guessed. Fleeing is the coward's way.
Shadowheart? Shadowheart? Where'd that girl run off to?
Huh. Where's Shadowheart?
Say, where's Lae'zel? She didn't abandon us, did she?
Hang on, where's Lae'zel? Feels wrong starting the day without anyone staring daggers at me.
No sign of Lae'zel. What happened?
Lae'zel? Lae'zel? Where's she run off to?
Huh. Where's Lae'zel?
She rushed off this morning. Wouldn't say why.
Oh, she probably wandered off to kill something adorable.
Say, where's Wyll? Bit early to be out hunting, isn't it?
Now - where's my favourite fella Wyll hiding?
The Blade of Frontiers has deserted his post? So much for legends.
No sign of Wyll. What happened to him?
Huh. Where's Wyll?

Synopsis: PAD when the player wakes up to find one of the party has disappeared during the night. Astarion knows what happened - they discovered that he's a vampire and left - but doesn't want to share that information.
